title: Mesoporous NiMoO4 nanorod electrode materials for flexible and asymmetric energy storage devices
content:
RSC Adv., 2024, 14,24749-24755
DOI: 10.1039/D4RA03352C, Paper
Open Access
  This article is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported Licence.
Qi He, Xingyu Liu, Xiang Wu
We synthesize NiMoO4-2 electrode material with a specific capacitance of 1194 F g−1 of 1 A g−1. The as-fabricated devices retain 89.2% of initial capacitance after 10 000 cycles.
